					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I get 4:59:90 in my emu.  I am using a CPU-cycle based counter as outlined by kevtris' doc.
<br />
<br />I, too, am interested in the actual cart's time.
<br />
<br />EDIT:
<br />
<br />I should also note that I'm using the shortest dip-switch set time (all switches open -- "5.001 mins" on kevtris' chart)
<br />
<br />I can only assume NEStopia is using a different configuration.  I suppose I'll try other settings too....
<br />
<br />I ran through with all my dipswitch settings in my emu and got:
<br />4:59:90
<br />5:17:50
<br />5:36:00
<br />5:55:10
<br />6:14:30  (NEStopia uses this setting I'd assume?)
<br />6:32:40
<br />6:51:10
<br />7:10:90
<br />7:29:60
<br />7:45:90
<br />8:08:10
<br />8:26:30
<br />8:45:30
<br />9:04:10
<br />9:23:20
<br />9:41:50
<br />
<br />I also noticed that I didn't get consistent times.  For example when I ran the short setting again, I got 4:59:50.  I wonder if when you press the button has an impact on when the IRQ will fire?</div>

